headline: The WSJ Dollar Index Falls 0.66% to 100.24
summary: The WSJ Dollar Index fell 0.66% to 100.24, the third-consecutive decline, as the U.S. PCE inflation data were in line with expectations.

headline: Treasury Yields, Dollar Little Changed by Unsurprising PCE Data
summary: The dollar remained weaker after PCE inflation data were in line with expectations. The yen gained on safe-heaven demand. The euro advanced after an ECB official defended a gradual approach to interest-rate cuts.
